   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"},\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"# Customer Complaint Category Prediction\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**NLP Project 6 of 100 · Beginner Text Classification**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This notebook builds a **multi-class text classifier** that predicts the category of a customer complaint from its text. We use the Banking77 dataset (77 fine-grained banking intents) grouped into 8 broader complaint categories, and compare TF-IDF baselines against ModernBERT.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Models:** TF-IDF + MultinomialNB (baseline), LogisticRegression, LinearSVC, SGDClassifier, RandomForest, ModernBERT\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Metrics:** Accuracy, Macro-F1, Per-class Precision/Recall, Confusion Matrix\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Load and explore a fine-grained intent classification dataset\\n\", \"2. Map 77 granular intents to broader complaint categories\\n\", \"3. Build TF-IDF baselines for multi-class complaint classification\\n\", \"4. Fine-tune ModernBERT for complaint categorization\\n\", \"5. Evaluate with macro-F1 and per-class metrics\\n\", \"6. Analyze which complaint types are hardest to distinguish\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Given a customer complaint text, classify it into one of 8 categories: **Card**, **Account**, **Transfer**, **Payment**, **ATM**, **Loan**, **Top-up**, or **Other**. This enables automated routing and prioritization.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Financial institutions receive millions of complaints. Manual categorization is slow and inconsistent.\\n\", \"- Automated complaint routing accelerates resolution and improves customer satisfaction.\\n\", \"- This teaches practical multi-class NLP with real-world label hierarchies.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|----------|-------|\\n\", \"| Source | HuggingFace `PolyAI/banking77` |\\n\", \"| Records | ~13,000 customer queries |\\n\", \"| Original classes | 77 fine-grained intents |\\n\", \"| Mapped to | 8 complaint categories |\\n\", \"| Language | English |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Source:** PolyAI Banking77 dataset, via HuggingFace\\n\", \"- **License:** CC BY 4.0\\n\", \"- Commonly used benchmark for intent detection in banking.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in ['pandas','numpy','matplotlib','seaborn','scikit-learn','datasets','transformers','accelerate','wordcloud']:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\n\", \"print('All packages ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import os, json, warnings, random, re\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\", \"from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression, SGDClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\n\", \"sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\", \"%matplotlib inline\\n\", \"print('Imports loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"SEED = 42\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.2\\n\", \"TFIDF_MAX_FEATURES = 10000\\n\", \"MODEL_NAME = 'answerdotai/ModernBERT-base'\\n\", \"MAX_LEN = 64\\n\", \"BATCH_SIZE = 32\\n\", \"EPOCHS = 3\\n\", \"LR = 2e-5\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Map 77 intents to 8 broader categories based on keyword patterns\\n\", \"def map_intent_to_category(intent):\\n\", \"    intent = intent.lower().replace('_', ' ')\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['card', 'pin', 'contactless', 'magnetic', 'virtual']): return 'Card'\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['account', 'verify', 'identity', 'passcode', 'password']): return 'Account'\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['transfer', 'exchange', 'currency', 'country']): return 'Transfer'\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['payment', 'cash', 'refund', 'charge', 'fee', 'direct debit']): return 'Payment'\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['atm', 'cash withdrawal']): return 'ATM'\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['loan', 'interest', 'credit']): return 'Loan'\\n\", \"    if any(w in intent for w in ['top up', 'top-up', 'topping']): return 'Top-up'\\n\", \"    return 'Other'\\n\", \"\\n\", \"random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\", \"SAVE_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath('__file__'))\\n\", \"print(f'Seed: {SEED}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"from datasets import load_dataset\\n\", \"ds = load_dataset('PolyAI/banking77')\\n\", \"train_df = ds['train'].to_pandas()\\n\", \"test_df = ds['test'].to_pandas()\\n\", \"print(f'Train: {train_df.shape}, Test: {test_df.shape}')\\n\", \"print(f'Columns: {list(train_df.columns)}')\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# The dataset has 'text' and 'label' (integer 0-76)\\n\", \"# Get label names from the dataset features\\n\", \"label_names_77 = ds['train'].features['label'].names\\n\", \"train_df['intent'] = train_df['label'].map(lambda x: label_names_77[x])\\n\", \"test_df['intent'] = test_df['label'].map(lambda x: label_names_77[x])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Map to broader categories\\n\", \"train_df['category'] = train_df['intent'].apply(map_intent_to_category)\\n\", \"test_df['category'] = test_df['intent'].apply(map_intent_to_category)\\n\", \"print(f'\\\\nCategory distribution:\\\\n{train_df[\\\"category\\\"].value_counts()}')\\n\", \"train_df[['text','intent','category']].head(10)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(f'Missing: {train_df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\\n\", \"print(f'Duplicates: {train_df.duplicated(subset=[\\\"text\\\"]).sum()}')\\n\", \"print(f'Categories: {sorted(train_df[\\\"category\\\"].unique())}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"train_df['text_len'] = train_df['text'].str.len()\\n\", \"train_df['word_count'] = train_df['text'].str.split().str.len()\\n\", \"LABEL_NAMES = sorted(train_df['category'].unique())\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\", \"for cat in LABEL_NAMES:\\n\", \"    sub = train_df[train_df['category']==cat]\\n\", \"    axes[0].hist(sub['text_len'], bins=30, alpha=0.4, label=cat)\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title('Text Length by Category'); axes[0].legend(fontsize=8)\\n\", \"train_df['category'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[1], color='steelblue', edgecolor='black')\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title('Category Distribution')\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, 'eda_distributions.png'), dpi=100, bbox_inches='tight')\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Classes are imbalanced — some categories have many more samples. We use `class_weight='balanced'` and macro-F1 for fair evaluation.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(f'Class proportions:\\\\n{(train_df[\\\"category\\\"].value_counts(normalize=True)*100).round(1)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Train/Validation/Test Split Strategy\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"le = LabelEncoder()\\n\", \"# Combine train+test and re-split for consistency\\n\", \"all_df = pd.concat([train_df, test_df], ignore_index=True)\\n\", \"all_df['label_enc'] = le.fit_transform(all_df['category'])\\n\", \"X = all_df['text'].values; y = all_df['label_enc'].values\\n\", \"X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y)\\n\", \"print(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}, Classes: {list(le.classes_)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TF-IDF with bigrams captures complaint-specific phrases. Banking queries are short and clean.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Feature Engineering\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=TFIDF_MAX_FEATURES, sublinear_tf=True, ngram_range=(1,2), min_df=2)\\n\", \"X_train_tfidf = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_test_tfidf = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"print(f'TF-IDF: {X_train_tfidf.shape}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model: TF-IDF + MultinomialNB\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"bl = MultinomialNB(alpha=0.5); bl.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train)\\n\", \"yp = bl.predict(X_test_tfidf)\\n\", \"print(f'Baseline Acc: {accuracy_score(y_test,yp):.4f}, Macro-F1: {f1_score(y_test,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\"):.4f}')\\n\", \"print(classification_report(y_test, yp, target_names=le.classes_))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Traditional ML Classifier Comparison\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> LazyPredict/FLAML not used for NLP classification per project conventions.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"clfs = {'MultinomialNB': MultinomialNB(alpha=0.5),\\n\", \"        'LogReg': LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED, class_weight='balanced'),\\n\", \"        'LinearSVC': CalibratedClassifierCV(LinearSVC(max_iter=2000, random_state=SEED, class_weight='balanced'), cv=3),\\n\", \"        'SGD': CalibratedClassifierCV(SGDClassifier(loss='hinge', random_state=SEED, class_weight='balanced', max_iter=1000), cv=3),\\n\", \"        'RF': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED, class_weight='balanced', n_jobs=-1)}\\n\", \"results = []; trained_models = {}\\n\", \"for name, clf in clfs.items():\\n\", \"    clf.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train); yp = clf.predict(X_test_tfidf)\\n\", \"    r = {'Model': name, 'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, yp), 'Macro_F1': f1_score(y_test, yp, average='macro')}\\n\", \"    results.append(r); trained_models[name] = (clf, yp)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"{name:15s} | Acc={r['Accuracy']:.4f} | Macro-F1={r['Macro_F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('Macro_F1', ascending=False)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Why FLAML AutoML Is Not Used Here\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> FLAML/LazyPredict are not applicable for NLP classification.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Transformer Approach: ModernBERT Fine-Tuning\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"transformer_results = None; y_pred_transformer = None\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    import torch\\n\", \"    from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForSequenceClassification, Trainer, TrainingArguments\\n\", \"    from datasets import Dataset\\n\", \"    device = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'; torch.manual_seed(SEED)\\n\", \"    num_labels = len(le.classes_)\\n\", \"    td = pd.DataFrame({'text': X_train, 'label': y_train})\\n\", \"    if len(td) > 8000: td = td.sample(n=8000, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"    tds = Dataset.from_pandas(td); eds = Dataset.from_pandas(pd.DataFrame({'text': X_test, 'label': y_test}))\\n\", \"    tok = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\\n\", \"    def tf_fn(ex): return tok(ex['text'], truncation=True, padding='max_length', max_length=MAX_LEN)\\n\", \"    tds = tds.map(tf_fn, batched=True); eds = eds.map(tf_fn, batched=True)\\n\", \"    tds.set_format('torch', columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\", \"    eds.set_format('torch', columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\", \"    model = AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME, num_labels=num_labels).to(device)\\n\", \"    args = TrainingArguments(output_dir='./out', num_train_epochs=EPOCHS, per_device_train_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\\n\", \"        per_device_eval_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE*2, warmup_ratio=0.1, weight_decay=0.01, learning_rate=LR,\\n\", \"        eval_strategy='epoch', save_strategy='no', logging_steps=50, report_to='none', seed=SEED, fp16=torch.cuda.is_available())\\n\", \"    def cm(ep): p=np.argmax(ep.predictions,axis=1); return {'accuracy':accuracy_score(ep.label_ids,p),'macro_f1':f1_score(ep.label_ids,p,average='macro')}\\n\", \"    trainer = Trainer(model=model, args=args, train_dataset=tds, eval_dataset=eds, compute_metrics=cm)\\n\", \"    print('Starting ModernBERT fine-tuning...'); trainer.train()\\n\", \"    po = trainer.predict(eds); y_pred_transformer = np.argmax(po.predictions, axis=1)\\n\", \"    transformer_results = {'Model': 'ModernBERT', 'Accuracy': accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_transformer),\\n\", \"        'Macro_F1': f1_score(y_test, y_pred_transformer, average='macro')}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"ModernBERT | Acc={transformer_results['Accuracy']:.4f} | Macro-F1={transformer_results['Macro_F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\", \"    del model, trainer; torch.cuda.empty_cache() if torch.cuda.is_available() else None\\n\", \"except Exception as e: print(f'Transformer skipped: {e}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"all_results = results.copy()\\n\", \"if transformer_results: all_results.append(transformer_results)\\n\", \"all_df = pd.DataFrame(all_results).sort_values('Macro_F1', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"print(all_df.to_string(index=False, float_format='{:.4f}'.format))\\n\", \"top3 = all_df.head(3)['Model'].tolist(); print(f'Top 3: {top3}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"top3d = {}\\n\", \"for n in top3:\\n\", \"    if n in trained_models: top3d[n] = trained_models[n][1]\\n\", \"    elif n == 'ModernBERT' and y_pred_transformer is not None: top3d[n] = y_pred_transformer\\n\", \"nc = len(top3d)\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, nc, figsize=(7*nc, 6))\\n\", \"if nc == 1: axes = [axes]\\n\", \"for i, (n, yp) in enumerate(top3d.items()):\\n\", \"    sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test, yp), annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',\\n\", \"                xticklabels=le.classes_, yticklabels=le.classes_, ax=axes[i])\\n\", \"    axes[i].set_title(n); axes[i].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, 'confusion_matrices.png'), dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\", \"for n, yp in top3d.items():\\n\", \"    print(f'\\\\n{n}'); print(classification_report(y_test, yp, target_names=le.classes_))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"bp = top3d.get(top3[0], bl.predict(X_test_tfidf))\\n\", \"edf = pd.DataFrame({'text': X_test, 'true': y_test, 'pred': bp})\\n\", \"edf['true_cat'] = le.inverse_transform(edf['true']); edf['pred_cat'] = le.inverse_transform(edf['pred'])\\n\", \"errs = edf[edf['true'] != edf['pred']]\\n\", \"print(f'Errors: {len(errs)}/{len(edf)} ({len(errs)/len(edf)*100:.1f}%)')\\n\", \"print(errs.groupby(['true_cat','pred_cat']).size().sort_values(ascending=False).head(5))\\n\", \"for _, r in errs.head(3).iterrows(): print(f'  {r[\\\"true_cat\\\"]}->{r[\\\"pred_cat\\\"]}: {r[\\\"text\\\"][:80]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Banking complaints have distinctive vocabulary per category.\\n\", \"2. Card vs Payment confusion is most common due to overlapping terminology.\\n\", \"3. TF-IDF baselines perform well because banking queries are short and keyword-rich.\\n\", \"4. ModernBERT helps with ambiguous queries that require contextual understanding.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Categories are derived from intent labels, not original complaint categories.\\n\", \"2. Short queries (1-2 sentences) are easier than full complaint emails.\\n\", \"3. English only. 4. No severity or urgency prediction.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## How to Improve\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Use CFPB real complaints. 2. Add severity prediction. 3. Multi-label for overlapping issues.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Sub-ms latency with TF-IDF. Confidence thresholds for human escalation.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Not handling class imbalance. 2. Over-splitting into too many categories. 3. No baseline.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Use all 77 original intents instead of 8 categories. 2. Add a priority score.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Complaint categorization is practical multi-class NLP.\\n\", \"2. Grouping fine-grained intents into categories is a common pattern.\\n\", \"3. TF-IDF + LogReg is fast and effective. ModernBERT handles edge cases.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"fm = {'project': 'Customer Complaint Category Prediction', 'task': 'multi_class_text_classification',\\n\", \"      'dataset': 'PolyAI/banking77', 'models': {}}\\n\", \"for r in all_results: fm['models'][r['Model']] = {k: round(v,4) if isinstance(v,float) else v for k,v in r.items() if k!='Model'}\\n\", \"mp = os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, 'metrics.json')\\n\", \"with open(mp, 'w') as f: json.dump(fm, f, indent=2)\\n\", \"print(f'Saved: {mp}'); print(json.dumps(fm, indent=2))\"]}\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
   ],
   "id": "10368a1f2d711127"
  }
 ],
